<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1400,1858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis box="[136,243,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Epiphytic</emphasis>
on the surface of living leaves. 
<emphasis box="[611,695,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Thallus</emphasis>
very thin, superficial, pale brown to brown walls. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1275,1444,1400,1426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[136,246,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Ascomata</emphasis>
gregarious to scattered, superficial, globose to subglobose, brown to dark brown, with indistinct ostiole. 
<emphasis box="[136,197,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Setae</emphasis>
abundant, corniform, brown, septate, constricted at septate, smooth-walled. 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1150,1472,1498]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Peraceae" genus="Peridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1150,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Peridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
composed of two sections, arranged in 
<emphasis box="[270,463,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">textura angularis</emphasis>
, outer layer of brown to dark brown, thick-walled cells, inner layer of light brown, thinwalled cells. 
<emphasis box="[284,332,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Asci</emphasis>
8-spored, bitunicate, obpyriform, rounded at the apex, sessile. 
<emphasis box="[1044,1171,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Ascospores</emphasis>
overlapping 2–3-seriate, hyaline, smooth-walled, fusoid, narrowly rounded at the ends, 3–4-septate, upper cells wider and shorter than lower cells, constricted at the septate, with a conspicuous mucilaginous sheath. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[974,1158,1616,1642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[1175,1285,1616,1642]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1175,1285,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Mycelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pale brown to brown at the apex, septate, constricted at septa, rough, thick-walled. 
<taxonomicName box="[913,1084,1652,1678]" class="Ascomycotina incertae sedis" family="Coelomycetous" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ascomycotina incertae sedis" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">
<emphasis box="[913,1084,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Coelomycetous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis box="[1099,1245,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Conidiomata</emphasis>
solitary, brown to dark brown, globose to subglobose. 
<emphasis box="[549,724,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Pycnidial walls</emphasis>
composed of pseudoparenchymatous cells of 
<emphasis box="[1249,1444,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">textura angularis</emphasis>
, outer layer brown to dark brown, thick-walled cell, inner layer with hyaline cells, thin-walled cells. 
<emphasis box="[1286,1451,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Conidiophores</emphasis>
reduced to conidiogenous cells. 
<emphasis box="[507,737,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
enteroblastic, phialidic, integrated, terminal, hyaline, smoothwalled. 
<taxonomicName box="[225,315,1796,1822]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Conidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[225,315,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Conidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
oblong to ellipsoid, hyaline, aseptate, guttulate, smooth-walled.
</paragraph>
